desc: Students consider a selected figure or movement from the history of philosophy. May be repeated if topics are different. Counts towards ancient studies and medieval studies majors. Prerequisites: two courses in philosophy, one of which must be either PHIL 235 or PHIL 236 or permission of the department chair.
